OL,3,CExplosion at military weapons factory
OL,5,FThe weapons factory site in Glascoed
OL,6,Fwas built in 1938 and established to
OL,7,Fhelp prepare the Royal Navy ahead of
OL,8,Fthe Second World War. It now employs
OL,9,Faround 500 people.
OL,11,FCommenting on today's explosion local
OL,12,FMP David Davies said:
OL,14,F"I have spoken at length with senior
OL,15,Fmanagement at BAE Systems. I
OL,16,Funderstand it was an explosion that
OL,17,Fhappened in a remote part of the site
OL,18,Fthat had been set aside to take apart
OL,19,Fshells and this was being done by
OL,20,Fremote control.
